Soloman Bygraves, 29, jailed for 30 months after admitting robbing 93-year-old Stanley Evans .
He offered to help Stanley with shopping but instead snatched his wallet and knocked him to the ground for ten minutes .
The pensioner was left lying in the entrance to his block of flats in Soho, central London .
Bygraves is homeless and has 21 convictions for 49 offences .